defaultI have never been able to see what benefit I derive, as a cyclist, from such road markings. I assume that it is supposed to make the cars keep out of the bike lane but I can assure you that the road markings make 
defaultno difference whatsoever to the clearance passing cars allow me. But the real concern is that if separation of cars and cycles is the rationale for such markings the fact that they disappear exactly at the point when they might deliver most benefit (the ro
defaultad narrowing) makes clear that these piece-meal 
